page.title: 18F of D Animal and Plant Life
page.content: {Fallow deer}can be seen in the woods in our area.There is a small{herd around{Staunton.They}are seen singly or in small groups and blend in well with the foliage.During spring there {calves}are born and{males shed their {antlers.}They do quite a bit of damage in gardens.The{fox}is common and if you're quiet it can often be seen in the{woods.Cubs}are born March/April. {Voles,Rabbits,Badgers,weasels,mice and{shrews}are found{too.Woodpeckers are heard drumming on branches and {owls}hoot at night.Much of the{ {woodland} is{coniferous}and{deciduous {trees. Bluebells}carpet the floor and {you can smell wild garlic during May. Wild{rasberries}and{strawberries}grow too.{Fern}is a{common plant.Lichens grow on higher parts of some trees-it means the air is reasonably free from pollution.
